Weather App
This is a web application that provides weather information for the user's current location and any searched city. It uses the OpenWeatherMap API to retrieve the weather data.

How to use
Load the web application.
If the browser supports geolocation and the user allows it, the application will retrieve the weather data for the user's current location.
If the user wants to search for weather data of a different city, they can enter the city name in the search bar and click the search button.
The application will display the current weather information for the chosen city and a 5-hour forecast and 7-day forecast for that city.
Technologies used
This application is built with the following technologies:

HTML
CSS
JavaScript
OpenWeatherMap API
How to set up
To set up this project, follow these steps:

Clone the repository.
Obtain an API key from OpenWeatherMap.
Open the script.js file in a text editor.
Replace the apikey variable value with the API key you obtained.
Save the file.
Open the index.html file in a web browser.
